<p>I need to force the xsi:type generation on fields because the xml will be deserialized into a different object through a xsl transformation sheet. Datatypes are defined with XSD schemas, anyone can use jaxb to generate classes and send data to the endpoint but the endpoint is completely dynamic and uses a special DTO containing common data fields and some Object maps which will hold the dynamic data fields. </p>  <p>For example this is what I get:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?&gt; &lt;myp:documento xmlns:myp="mypns" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"&gt;   &lt;myp:sys_name&gt;name&lt;/myp:sys_name&gt;   &lt;myp:sys_path&gt;path&lt;/myp:sys_path&gt;   &lt;myp:sys_type&gt;type&lt;/myp:sys_type&gt;   &lt;myp:dyn_date_modified&gt;2015-09-30T11:13:10.810+02:00&lt;/myp:dyn_date_modified&gt; &lt;/myp:documento&gt; </code></pre>  <p>this is what I need:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?&gt; &lt;myp:documento xmlns:myp="mypns" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"&gt;   &lt;myp:sys_name&gt;name&lt;/myp:sys_name&gt;   &lt;myp:sys_path&gt;path&lt;/myp:sys_path&gt;   &lt;myp:sys_type&gt;type&lt;/myp:sys_type&gt;   &lt;myp:dyn_date_modified xsi:type="xs:dateTime"&gt;2015-09-30T11:13:10.810+02:00&lt;/myp:dyn_date_modified&gt; &lt;/myp:documento&gt; </code></pre>  <p>because the attribute <code>dyn_date_modified</code> will be deserialized into the dynamic Object map..</p>  <p>Let me know if you need more detail.</p>